zDocsExportTopicButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"singlePdf\" role=\"button\">Save selected topic</a><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportSubtopicsButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"pdfWithChildren\" role=\"button\">Save selected topic and subtopics</a><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportBundleButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"wholeBundlePdf\" role=\"button\">Save entire publication</a></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicShare zDocsShareButton\" role=\"listitem\"><span aria-expanded=\"false\" aria-label=\"Share\" class=\"d-none d-lg-flex zDocsShareDialogButton\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" data-tooltip-content=\"Share\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsTopicActionsTooltip\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-share\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-share\"></use></svg></span><span class=\"d-lg-none zDocsShareDialogButton\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-share\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-share\"></use></svg>Share</span><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu\"><a class=\"dropdown-item zDocsShareButton zDocsShareEmail\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\"><span>Email Link</span></a><a class=\"dropdown-item zDocsShareButton zDocsShareLink\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\"><span>Copy Link</span></a></div></div><div class=\"zDocsFeedback zDocsFeedback zDocsTopicFeedback\" role=\"listitem\"><span aria-label=\"Feedback\" class=\"zDocsFeedbackButton d-none d-lg-flex\" data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_3613406\" data-toggle=\"modal\" data-tooltip-content=\"Feedback\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsTopicActionsTooltip\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg></span><span class=\"d-lg-none d-flex zDocsFeedbackButton\" data-backdrop=\"static\" data-return-focus=\"#zDocsTopicActionsMobile\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_3613406\" data-toggle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Jan 03, 2025</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104gya1665702610097.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/gya1665702610097.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/gya1665702610097.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"gya1665702610097\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n      Frame </h1>\n<div class=\"body conbody\" id=\"gya1665702610097__frame_314323\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">A Frame is a Development Object that graphically represents a Development Object in\n      the layout of a Form or Report component. </p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"gya1665702610097__p_d95741e1_d95742e1_d95743e1\">Frames are used to represent component entities, fields,\n         and labels. There are also specialized frames for objects that occur only in forms and\n         reports, such as lines, area frames, and print frames.</p>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"gya1665702610097__topic_d63917e1_d63918e1_d63919e1_d63920e1_d63921e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d608250e56\"> Characteristics </h2>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table class=\"table\" count-columns=\"2\" id=\"gya1665702610097__table_d10625e1_d10626e1_d10627e1\"><caption></caption><colgroup><col/><col/></colgroup><thead class=\"thead\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"gya1665702610097__table_d10625e1_d10626e1_d10627e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">Characteristics</p>\n</th>\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"gya1665702610097__table_d10625e1_d10626e1_d10627e1__entry__2\"></th>\n</tr>\n</thead><tbody class=\"tbody\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"gya1665702610097__table_d10625e1_d10626e1_d10627e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">Icon:</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"gya1665702610097__table_d10625e1_d10626e1_d10627e1__entry__2\">\n<p class=\"p\"><img alt=\"Icon\" class=\"image\" id=\"gya1665702610097__image_skl_tr4_mwb\" src=\"https://docs-be.rocketsoftware.com/bundle/uniface_104/page/frame_area.png?_LANG=enus\"/></p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"gya1665702610097__table_d10625e1_d10626e1_d10627e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">Object type code:</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"gya1665702610097__table_d10625e1_d10626e1_d10627e1__entry__2\">\n<p class=\"p\">—</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"gya1665702610097__table_d10625e1_d10626e1_d10627e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">Main Development Object?</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"gya1665702610097__table_d10625e1_d10626e1_d10627e1__entry__2\">\n<p class=\"p\">No</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"gya1665702610097__table_d10625e1_d10626e1_d10627e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">Part of:</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"gya1665702610097__table_d10625e1_d10626e1_d10627e1__entry__2\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"euw1665702582150.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/euw1665702582150.html\" title=\"A Form is a stateful presentation Component that enables users to view and modify data in a Windows or character mode application.\">Form</a>, <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"rvk1665702582227.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/rvk1665702582227.html\" title=\"A Report is a Component that defines the content and layout of printed output of a Uniface application. It is not interactive and cannot be used to update the database.\">Report</a>\n</p>\n<p class=\"p\">, <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"yth1665702550544.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/yth1665702550544.html\" title=\"A Component Entity is a Development Object that represents data that is owned by a Component. It is part of the Component’s structure and is maintained as part of the Component, although it may reference and inherit from a Modeled Entity.\">Component Entity</a>, <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"jxb1665702610180.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/jxb1665702610180.html\" title=\"A Print Header is a Frame in a Form or Report component that is used to print information at the top of each printed page.\">Print Header</a>,\n                              <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"jfg1665702610254.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/jfg1665702610254.html\" title=\"A Print Footer is a Frame in a Form or Report component that is used to print information at the bottom of each printed page.\">Print Footer</a>, <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"cjb1665702610334.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/cjb1665702610334.html\" title=\"A Break Frame is a development object in a Form or Report component that is used to display conditional information when a page break is encountered. A component can have multiple break frames.\">Break Frame</a>\n</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"gya1665702610097__table_d10625e1_d10626e1_d10627e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">Contains:</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"gya1665702610097__table_d10625e1_d10626e1_d10627e1__entry__2\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"jgi1665702550212.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/jgi1665702550212.html\" title=\"A Property is a named, typed attribute of Development Object that defines a characteristic or behavior of the object. Each property has a descriptive name, a literal name, a data type, and a value. If no value is specified, a default value may be used.\">Property</a>, <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"cny1665702550298.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/cny1665702550298.html\" title=\"A Code Container is a type of Property that holds code, such as ProcScript, JavaScript, or HTML. It can contain one or more code modules, such as triggers, operations, functions, or entries, or HTML for the layout.\">Code Container</a>,\n                              <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"eyt1681415255117.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/eyt1681415255117.html\" title=\"An area is a development object that represents an area frame on a Form or Report component. It is used to group objects and style the area it encloses.\">Area</a>\n</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"gya1665702610097__table_d10625e1_d10626e1_d10627e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">Generalization:</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"gya1665702610097__table_d10625e1_d10626e1_d10627e1__entry__2\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"ulo1665702550460.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/ulo1665702550460.html\" title=\"A Uniface Development Object is an abstract data type that defines the characteristics and behavior of a logical application unit, such as a Component, Field, Message, Library, and so on.\">Development Object</a>\n</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"gya1665702610097__table_d10625e1_d10626e1_d10627e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">Specializations:</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"gya1665702610097__table_d10625e1_d10626e1_d10627e1__entry__2\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"eyt1681415255117.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/eyt1681415255117.html\" title=\"An area is a development object that represents an area frame on a Form or Report component. It is used to group objects and style the area it encloses.\">Area</a>, <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"jxb1665702610180.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/jxb1665702610180.html\" title=\"A Print Header is a Frame in a Form or Report component that is used to print information at the top of each printed page.\">Print Header</a>,\n                              <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"jfg1665702610254.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/jfg1665702610254.html\" title=\"A Print Footer is a Frame in a Form or Report component that is used to print information at the bottom of each printed page.\">Print Footer</a>, <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"cjb1665702610334.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/cjb1665702610334.html\" title=\"A Break Frame is a development object in a Form or Report component that is used to display conditional information when a page break is encountered. A component can have multiple break frames.\">Break Frame</a>,\n                              <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"gxr1665702610494.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/gxr1665702610494.html\" title=\"An Area is a Development Object that defines a vertical or horizontal line in the layout of a Form or Report component.\">Line</a>, <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"yth1665702550544.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/yth1665702550544.html\" title=\"A Component Entity is a Development Object that represents data that is owned by a Component. It is part of the Component’s structure and is maintained as part of the Component, although it may reference and inherit from a Modeled Entity.\">Component Entity</a>,\n                              <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"zyj1665702550619.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/zyj1665702550619.html\" title=\"A Component Field is a Development Object that represents a unit of data in a Component Entity.\">Component Field</a>, <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"wyt1665702609153.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/wyt1665702609153.html\" title=\"A Label is a Development Object that contains text that appears on a presentation component. Labels have properties, but most cannot be set dynamically.\">Label</a>\n</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"gya1665702610097__table_d10625e1_d10626e1_d10627e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">Compilation Output:</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"gya1665702610097__table_d10625e1_d10626e1_d10627e1__entry__2\">\n<p class=\"p\">—</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"gya1665702610097__table_d10625e1_d10626e1_d10627e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">URI format:</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"gya1665702610097__table_d10625e1_d10626e1_d10627e1__entry__2\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">are:<var class=\"keyword varname\">AreaId</var>\n</code>\n</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody></table></div>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"gya1665702610097__p_d95747e1_d95748e1_d95749e1\">A Frame is an abstract, complex data type that has the\n            following characteristics,</p>\n<ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"gya1665702610097__li_d38618e1_d38619e1_d38620e1\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"gya1665702610097__p_d95750e1_d95751e1_d95752e1\">It can have a parent development object.</p>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"gya1665702610097__li_d38621e1_d38622e1_d38623e1\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"gya1665702610097__p_d95753e1_d95754e1_d95755e1\">It can have can have three types of\n                  children:</p>\n<ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"gya1665702610097__li_d38624e1_d38625e1_d38626e1\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"gya1665702610097__p_d95756e1_d95757e1_d95758e1\"><dfn class=\"term\">Properties</dfn>, including  Name,  Description and  Comment, and other properties that are specific to its\n                        type.</p>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"gya1665702610097__li_d38627e1_d38628e1_d38629e1\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"gya1665702610097__p_d95759e1_d95760e1_d95761e1\"><dfn class=\"term\">Code containers</dfn>, which are\n                        type-specific properties that hold ProcScript, JavaScript, or HTML.</p>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"gya1665702610097__li_d38630e1_d38631e1_d38632e1\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"gya1665702610097__p_d95762e1_d95763e1_d95764e1\">Other development objects.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"gya1665702610097__li_d38633e1_d38634e1_d38635e1\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"gya1665702610097__p_d95765e1_d95766e1_d95767e1\">It has a case-insensitive identifier that is\n                  unique for its type.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"gya1665702610097__p_d95768e1_d95769e1_d95770e1\">Each object is uniquely identified by its type,\n                  parent names, and name. Objects of a different type can have the same name.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/ujj1665702610581.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Area Frames and Lines</a><p>Area frames are objects that can be used to group or separate the contents of a Form component.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/ljw1665702610670.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Area Frames for Printing</a><p>In reports, area frames can be used to add and protect text as part of an entity in Report components.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_3613406\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_3613406\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Frame Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Jan 03, 2025 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Frame A Frame is a Development Object that graphically represents a Development Object in the layout of a Form or Report component. Frames are used to represent component entities, fields, and labels. There are also specialized frames for objects that occur only in forms and reports, such as lines, area frames, and print frames. Characteristics Characteristics Icon: Object type code: — Main Development Object? No Part of: Form , Report , Component Entity , Print Header , Print Footer , Break Frame Contains: Property , Code Container , Area Generalization: Development Object Specializations: Area , Print Header , Print Footer , Break Frame , Line , Component Entity , Component Field , Label Compilation Output: — URI format: are: AreaId A Frame is an abstract, complex data type that has the following characteristics, It can have a parent development object. It can have can have three types of children: Properties , including Name, Description and Comment, and other properties that are specific to its type. Code containers , which are type-specific properties that hold ProcScript, JavaScript, or HTML. Other development objects. It has a case-insensitive identifier that is unique for its type. Each object is uniquely identified by its type, parent names, and name. Objects of a different type can have the same name. Related Links Area Frames and Lines Area frames are objects that can be used to group or separate the contents of a Form component. Area Frames for Printing In reports, area frames can be used to add and protect text as part of an entity in Report components. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}